The linear approximation, $L(x)$, to a function, $f(x)$, at the point
$a$, is given by

\begin{align*}\displaystyle
L(x) = f(a) + f'(a)(x - a).\end{align*}

From the information given we can write the linear approximation to the
function $f(x) = x^{1/3}$ at $a = 8$ as follows:

\begin{align*}
L(x) &= 8^{1/3} + \frac{1}{3}8^{-2/3}(x - 8) \\
&= 2 + \frac{1}{12}(x - 8).\end{align*}

Thus, the linear approximation gives us the approximate value for
$(7.5)^{1/3}$:

\begin{align*}
(7.5)^{1/3} \approx L(7.5) &= 2 + \frac{1}{12}(7.5 - 8) \\
&= 2 - \frac{1}{24} \\
&= \frac{47}{24}.\end{align*}

(This answer is already expressed in lowest terms.)
